Question 1:  Write a simple program in HTML  that displays the heading "HTML defines the content and structure of your website‚Äù on the web browser.

Ans.:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Heading tag</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>HTML defines the content and structure of your website</h1>
</body>
</html>




Question 2:  Explain the purpose of comments in HTML and provide an example of how to use comments in an HTML document.

Ans.:    Comments in HTML are used to add notes or explanations within the code that are not displayed on the webpage. 
         They help developers understand the code, provide reminders, and make the code easier to read and maintain.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Heading tag</title>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- This is a heading -->
    <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>

    <!-- This paragraph explains the purpose of the site -->
    <h1>HTML defines the content and structure of your website</h1>

    <!-- TODO: Add more sections here later -->

</body>
</html>





Question 3:   Write an HTML program that includes a heading, a paragraph of text, a horizontal line, and a line break. Arrange these elements to create a simple web page layout.

Ans.:


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Heading tag</title>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- This is a heading -->
    <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>

    <hr>  <!-- Horizontal Line -->

    <!-- This paragraph explains the purpose of the site -->
    <h1>HTML defines the content and structure of your website</h1>

    <!-- Paragraph -->
    <p>This is a simple paragraph of text that gives information about the page.</p>  

    <hr>  <!-- Horizontal Line 2 -->

    <!-- Line Break -->
    <p> This is another paragraph. <br> Here is a new line using the line break tag. </p> 

</body>
</html>




Question 4:    Write a short note on Tag and element with an example.

Ans.:      A tag is a keyword inside angle brackets (< >) that defines an HTML element, such as <p> for a paragraph. 
           An element consists of an opening tag, content, and a closing tag. For example, in 
            
           <p>This is a paragraph.</p> 

           <p> is the opening tag, </p> is the closing tag, and this is a paragraph. is the content. 
           Together, they form a paragraph element.





Question 5:   What is the DOCTYPE Declaration in HTML?

Ans.:         The DOCTYPE declaration in HTML (<!DOCTYPE html>) tells the web browser which version of HTML the document is using. It must be the first line in an HTML file.









